###Assembly
Fit 2 cm of hose into the cyclone and apply hot glue around the edges of the cyclone to secure the two together and provide an air-tight seal
Assemble the aperture according to the design manual
Screw the aperture on the end of the nozzle
Glue the other end of the nozzle into the cyclone inlet
Create a stand using wooden beams
Use three wood planks to make a U shape. The horizontal plank is 14 inches wide to match the width of a standard conveyor belt.
Glue the vertical beams to the horizontal base and side of cyclone
Attach clamps to the horizontal base
Attach the collection bag to the outlet of the cyclone with glue/tape
Clamp base to the side of the conveyor belt
